acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

params._supportedTokens: Initial set of whitelisted payment tokens.

depositRevenue(uint256,address,uint256).details: Caller must have approved this contract to spend `amount` of `paymentToken`.      Typically called by the agent's backend after receiving an x402 payment.

params.agentId: The agent that earned this revenue.
params.paymentToken: The ERC-20 token received (must be whitelisted).

distribute(uint256,address).details: Anyone can call this  permissionless distribution incentivises liveness.      Split: platformFee  treasury, buybackShare  held, agentShare  agentWallet.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

rescueTokens(address,address,uint256).details: Only callable by the owner. Cannot rescue tokens that are allocated as buyback funds.

transferOwnership(address).details: Starts the ownership transfer of the contract to a new account. Replaces the pending transfer if there is one. Can only be called by the current owner. Setting `newOwner` to the zero address is allowed; this can be used to cancel an initiated ownership transfer.

withdrawBuybackFunds(uint256,address,add.details: The owner is responsible for executing the actual buyback off-chain or via a separate contract.      This keeps the RevenueRouter simple and avoids coupling to DEX-specific logic.

params.paymentToken: The payment token to withdraw buyback funds for.

buybackBps().notice: Percentage of post-fee revenue allocated to buyback (3000 = 30%).

depositRevenue(uint256,address,uint256).notice: Deposit x402 revenue for a specific agent.

distribute(uint256,address).notice: Distribute all undistributed revenue for an agent in a given token.

getAvailableBuyback(uint256,address).notice: Get the buyback funds available for withdrawal.

getRevenue(uint256,address).notice: Get the full revenue record for an agent + token pair.

getUndistributed(uint256,address).notice: Get the amount available for distribution.

identityRegistry().notice: Convenience: get the identity registry from the factory.

rescueTokens(address,address,uint256).notice: Rescue tokens accidentally sent to this contract (not part of any agent's buyback).

treasury().notice: Platform treasury that receives the platform fee.

withdrawBuybackFunds(uint256,address,add.notice: Withdraw accumulated buyback funds. Only callable by the agent owner.
